    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-04-01T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-04-01T12:00:00-05:00" n="837"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d837">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.48 Earthquake of 1931/16: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lay</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-01T11:00:00-06:00"
                            >April 1, 1931—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>56. Have sent Naval Attaché Geyer to Managua this morning to assist relief work
                    by Tela Railroad Company plane which is carrying repairs for radio station
                    there.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lay</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
